## MITRE ATT&CK CWE Mapping (Key Entries)

| CWE | ATT&CK Technique |
|-----|-----------------|
| CWE-89 (SQLi) | T1190 — Exploit Public-Facing Application |
| CWE-79 (XSS) | T1059.007 — JavaScript |
| CWE-22 (Path Traversal) | T1083 — File and Directory Discovery |
| CWE-78 (OS Command Injection) | T1059 — Command and Scripting Interpreter |
| CWE-502 (Deserialization) | T1190 — Exploit Public-Facing Application |
| CWE-918 (SSRF) | T1090 — Proxy |

## Important Notes

- **CISA KEV is the strongest signal.** If a CVE is in the KEV, treat as confirmed dangerous regardless of other scores.
- **EPSS scores change daily.** The model updates every 24 hours. A low EPSS today doesn't stay low.
- **OSV covers open-source ecosystems only.** Use NVD as fallback for proprietary software.
- **For large batches (50+ CVEs):** Expect 5-6 minutes of enrichment time due to NVD rate limits.

